Privacy Policy
Last updated: January 22, 2025
Thank you for using the IELTS Preparation Assistant app (“we,” “us,” or “our”). Your privacy is important to us, and we are committed to protecting it. This policy explains how we collect, use, share, and safeguard your personal information when you use our mobile applications.
By using our apps or services, you agree to this Privacy Policy. Please read it carefully. If you have any questions, feel free to contact us.
1. Information We Collect
Personal Information
We may collect personal details you provide, such as your name and email address, when you create an account or contact us. We use this information to:
Register and manage your account
Respond to your inquiries or feedback
Usage Data
We automatically gather certain information when you use our apps, such as:
Your IP address
Device type and operating system
App usage patterns (pages or screens visited)
This helps us better understand how you interact with our services and improve app performance.
2. How We Use Your Data
Provide and Maintain Services:
Ensure our apps work as intended.
Account Management:
Create, manage, or update your user account.
Product Improvement:
Analyze usage data to fix issues and develop new features.
Communication:
Send app updates or important notices related to your account.
OpenAI API Services:
Some features use OpenAI’s API. Any text or data you input into these features may be sent to OpenAI to process your request.
3. Analytics
Google Analytics & Firebase
We use services like Google Analytics and Firebase to understand how you interact with our apps. These services collect data such as usage frequency, the type of device you use, and other relevant information to help us improve our app performance and user experience.
4. Your Choices
Data Collection:
We do not currently provide an option for you to opt out of analytics. By using the app, you consent to our data collection as described in this policy.
Update or Delete Information:
If you want to review, update, or delete your personal data, please contact us using the details below.
5. Data Security
We use industry-standard measures to protect your information. However, no system is 100% secure. By using our services, you acknowledge and accept this inherent risk.
6. Changes to This Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices or for legal reasons. The latest version will always be available on this page.
7. Contact Us
If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy or your data, please email us at
hi@inviral.tech
